        "content": "<p>Currently, in Mathlib, the predicate of \"subset\" <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/bc0b6c6f9d571e5edf0bdbaaf69857f509b62465/Mathlib/Data/Set/Defs.lean#L64-L68\">is defined as</a>:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"bp\">∀</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">⦃</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">⦄,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∈</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">s₁</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∈</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">s₂</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Note that we currently have <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/5d3df7b5f45fa4781edd56c9b8869c49f89b820c/src/Init/BinderPredicates.lean\">\"binder predicates\"</a>, i.e.:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"bp\">∀</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∈</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">s₁</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∈</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">s₂</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>But these two versions differ in the explicitness of <code>a</code>. I wonder if we should support either of the following syntaxes:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code>∀ ⦃a⦄ ∈ s₁, a ∈ s₂</code></li>\n<li><code>∀ ⦃a ∈ s₁⦄, a ∈ s₂</code></li>\n</ul>",
        "id": 543071902,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1759568276
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This is a very common use case and it has been suggested before that <code>∀ a ∈ s, p a</code> could actually just mean <code>∀ ⦃a⦄, a ∈ s → p a</code>. Indeed, the other (=current) interpretation <code>∀ a, a ∈ s → p a</code> seems to be heuristically never useful</p>",
        "id": 543072730,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1759569171
    }
]